A foreign national was reported kidnapped early Tuesday morning at a construction site at Dangi Roundabout, Zaria Road in Kano. A reliable source told The Guardian the kidnappers instantly short dead a Nigeria driver at the spot before the expatriate was whisked to an unknown destination. The expatriate is believed to be one of the engineers of Triacta construction company handling the multi-billion underpass state government project on Dangi roundabout adjacent Zoo road in Kano metropolis. Kano State police spokesman Haruna Abdullahi confirmed the development. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .